# Google Calendar API v3
# Docs: https://developers.google.com/calendar/api/v3/reference
#
# Token: GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN is short-lived (~1h). To refresh, see the
# `api-tests` skill — it walks sc_id → refresh_token → fresh access_token,
# either off-DB (read-only, prod-safe) or write-back (local only).
#
# Param cheat sheet (used by /events below):
#   singleEvents=false  → masters + exceptions; required for orderBy=updated.
#   singleEvents=true   → expanded occurrences; required for orderBy=startTime.
#   timeMin / timeMax   → ISO 8601 RFC 3339; use ...Z for UTC.
#   maxResults          → default 250, cap 2500.
#   syncToken           → from a prior response; returns delta only.
#
# Useful jq slices:
#   calendarList:         jq '.items[] | {id, summary, primary, accessRole}'
#   calendarList colors:  jq '.items[] | {id, summary, colorId, backgroundColor, foregroundColor}'
#   events:               jq '.items[] | {id, summary, start, end, recurrence}'

### List the user's calendars
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/users/me/calendarList
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### Get one calendar's metadata
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID}}
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### Get the color palette (event.colorId "1".."11" → hex)
# Event objects carry a string `colorId`; resolve via `event.<id>.background`.
# Calendar-level color (when an event has no colorId of its own) lives in
# `calendar.<id>` keyed by the calendarList entry's `colorId`.
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/colors
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### List events — masters + exceptions (best for sync fidelity)
# Recurring masters carry a `recurrence` field; modified instances appear as
# exceptions. orderBy=updated requires singleEvents=false.
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID}}/events?singleEvents=false&orderBy=updated&maxResults=250
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### List events — expanded occurrences in a date range (best for "what shows on day X")
# Each recurring instance becomes its own row (no `recurrence` field).
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID}}/events?singleEvents=true&orderBy=startTime&timeMin=2026-04-25T00:00:00Z&timeMax=2026-05-25T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### Get a single event by id
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID}}/events/{{GOOGLE_EVENT_ID}}
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### Incremental sync (use syncToken from a previous full list response)
GET https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID}}/events?syncToken=PUT_TOKEN_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}

### Watch a calendar (push notifications)
POST https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3/calendars/{{GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID}}/events/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{GOOGLE_OAUTH_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "test-channel-id-uuid",
  "type": "web_hook",
  "address": "https://example.com/webhook"
}
